    Plate: Splashed-Ink Landscape (\u30772?\u22696?\u23665?\u27700?)\par
\cf3\i     [credit: Sessh\u363? T\u333?y\u333? \u183? 1495 \u183? Tokyo National Museum \u183? Public domain]\i0\cf0\par
    Why we are looking at this:\par
    A landscape made of almost nothing. A boat. A roof. A mountain implied by what the painter chose not to paint. Sessh\u363? made this at seventy-six, after a lifetime of making more careful pictures. The discipline of leaving things out is acquired, not natural. We are born adding.\par
