\par\par\cf2\b\f2\fs32 \u9619?\u9619?\u9619? 26 III-TWELVE SUBTRACTIONS\b0\f0\fs28\cf0\par
\cf3\i     [slow enumeration; one beat per item]\i0\cf0\par
\par
\cf3\i     [kicker: \u8961? A list]\i0\cf0\par
    12\par
\par
    Subtractions that improve almost any life.\par
\par
    Most self-help is addition. Add a habit. Add a tool. Add a vitamin. A book that only adds is a book that does not respect your time. Here is a list of removals. They cost nothing. They compound.\par
\par
    \u8226? One social platform you do not enjoy. Today.\par
    \u8226? One recurring meeting that has produced nothing in four weeks.\par
    \u8226? One chair you sit in too often, that is shaped like an apology.\par
    \u8226? One acquaintance who only calls when something has gone wrong for them.\par
    \u8226? One subscription you forgot you had. Probably two.\par
    \u8226? One opinion you have repeated for years that you would not, today, hold for the first time.\par
    \u8226? One adjective from your professional bio.\par
    \u8226? One project you began with a borrowed enthusiasm.\par
    \u8226? One container of takeaway sauce in the back of the fridge.\par
    \u8226? One unread newsletter, every Sunday morning, without reading it first.\par
    \u8226? One word from every paragraph you write. Then one more.\par
    \u8226? One day a week from your calendar \u8212? given back to no one, kept for nothing in particular.\par
\par
\par\par\cf2\b\f2\fs32 \u9619?\u9619?\u9619? 27 III-ARDEN EMPTY CUP\b0\f0\fs28\cf0\par
