    Things that take longer than you think, and should.\par
\par
    Most regret is the regret of a thing rushed. Here is a list of things to give time to. None of them care about your schedule.\par
\par
    \u8226? A friendship that has not yet had its third real conversation.\par
    \u8226? A book about a place you have not been to.\par
    \u8226? A new language, accepted as a slow lifelong roommate, not a sprint.\par
    \u8226? A grief, allowed to take the season it asked for.\par
    \u8226? A child's question, answered fully, not in passing.\par
    \u8226? A meal cooked from raw ingredients, with no music.\par
    \u8226? A sentence you suspect is not yet true. Wait until it is.\par
    \u8226? The decision about whether to leave a city.\par
    \u8226? The decision about whether to stay.\par
    \u8226? Tea. Always tea. Until the tea tells you it is done.\par
\par
